158 SECTION 1-3.
159 Said title is further amended by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
160 "43-1-3.1.
161 (a) As used in this Code section, the term 'license' means any license, certificate, permit,
162 registration, or other document that is issued by a professional licensing board and that is
163 required under this title for a person to engage in the practice of a profession, business, or
164 trade in this state. Such term shall include, without limitation, any expedited license,
165 temporary license, special license, or license by endorsement that is issued by a
166 professional licensing board under this title.
167 (b)(1) Notwithstanding any provision of this title to the contrary, the division director
168 shall be authorized to review each application for the issuance, renewal, or reinstatement
169 of a license and, upon determining that an application furnishes evidence that the
170 applicant has achieved or satisfied all of the qualifications, attainments, and other
171 conditions required for the issuance, renewal, or reinstatement of a particular license
172 under the provisions of this title or under the rules and regulations promulgated pursuant
