173 to this title, shall be authorized, on behalf of the applicable professional licensing board,
174 to issue the license to or renew or reinstate the license of the applicant.
175 (2) Whenever the division director reviews any application for the issuance, renewal, or
176 reinstatement of a license pursuant to paragraph (1) of this subsection and cannot
177 determine, based on such application, that the applicant has achieved or satisfied all of
178 the qualifications, attainments, and other conditions required for the issuance, renewal,
179 or reinstatement of the license under the provisions of this title or under the rules and
180 regulations promulgated pursuant to this title, the division director shall not take any
181 action on the application and shall forward the application to the applicable professional
182 licensing board who shall then review, consider, and either grant or deny the application
183 in a timely manner.
184 (c) Nothing in this Code section shall prevent a professional licensing board from
185 reviewing applications for the issuance, renewal, or reinstatement of a license that is issued
186 by such professional licensing board and granting or denying such applications. Any such
187 application which a professional licensing board has granted or denied shall not be
188 reviewed or considered by the division director and, if the division director is in the process
189 of reviewing or considering such application at the time the professional licensing board
190 grants or denies such application, the division director shall cease his or her review of such
191 application and shall not take any further action on the application.
192 (d) When it is necessary for the division director, in connection with his or her review of
193 an application for the issuance, renewal, or reinstatement of a license under subsection (b)
194 of this Code section, to determine whether the applicant has satisfied any postsecondary
