203 SECTION 1-4.
204 Said title is further amended by revising Code Section 43-1-4, relating to expiration, renewal,
205 and penalty dates of licenses and certificates; duration of validity, and renewals, as follows:
206 "43-1-4.
207 (a) The division director shall determine the expiration, renewal, and penalty dates for
208 each license and certificate issued by the professional licensing boards through the office
209 of the division director which is subject to renewal. Before becoming effective, these
210 expiration, renewal, and penalty dates must be approved by the respective professional
211 licensing boards.
212 (b) Each Notwithstanding any provision of this title to the contrary, each license and
213 certificate issued by the professional licensing boards through the office of the division
214 director which are subject to renewal shall be valid for up to two years and shall be
215 renewable biennially on the renewal date established by the division director, as approved
216 by the respective professional licensing boards. Any such license or certificate shall be
217 renewable for up to 45 days after the expiration of such license or certificate, provided that
218 the licensee or the certificate holder has satisfied all requirements and paid all fees relating
219 to the renewal of such license or certificate as provided in this title or in the rules and
220 regulations promulgated pursuant to this title.
221 (c) The division director is authorized to adopt the necessary rules and regulations to
222 implement the biennial renewal of licenses and certificates in such manner as to ensure that
223 the number of renewals is reasonably evenly distributed throughout each two-year period."
